    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Jehan François (?) (Augsburg, 8 October
                    1530)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1"> He got to know from Elek Thurzó’s letter what great
                            devastation the Turks have inflicted on Moravia and Hungary. 40,000
                            people were slaughtered or taken into servitude; on the Thurzós’
                            territory they have found 500 children dead, brutally slaughtered.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15301008_2_1.jog"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad <persName>Ioannem Franciscum</persName><note xml:id="note.1"
                        >Probably Jehan François or Hans Franc who was inspector of Ravenstein and
                        Seneschal of Queen Mary, see <hi rend="smallcap">Gorter van Royen</hi> 2009,
                        74–75, 94, and <hi rend="smallcap">Kerkhoff</hi> 2008, 294.</note>. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Cum essem sollicitus intelligere, quantum <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >Turcae</del> damni aut incendii <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert"
                        >Turcae</add> in Moravia et Hungaria, ubi iter fecerunt, commisissent,
                    venerunt litterae ab <persName>Alexio Turzone</persName><note xml:id="note.2"
                        >Thurzó also wrote on the devastation to the city of Bratislava, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Erdélyi</hi> 2005, 216–217.</note>, quae significabant
                    Ioannis de Broda<note xml:id="note.3">On the looting in Brod see Ep.
                            94.<ref>olahus.tei.15301008_1</ref></note> Moravi bona omnia esse
                    combusta. Quadraginta vel circiter millia hominum, partim Hungarorum, partim
                        <del corresp="Olahus">Moraviorum Turcas abduxisse. Tres</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Moravorum a Turcis partim interfecta, partim
                        in servitutem perpetuam abducta. Tres</add></p>
                <pb facs="15301008_2_2.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">habuisse eosdem in bonis Turzonis consessus, vel potius descensus,
                    in quolibet <del corresp="Olahus">concessu</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="corr">consessu</add> repertos circiter quingentos infantes partim
                    dissectos, partim in terram collisos. Haec est <del corresp="Olahus">Deus bene
                        humanitas</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">crudelitas</add> Turcarum.
                    Vale et memineris, quibus malis Deus nos merito pro nostris delictis puniat.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Ex <placeName>Augusta</placeName> VIII. Octobris MDXXX.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
